OL,6,FSenior figures from G4S and the Prison
OL,7,FService have been giving evidence to
OL,8,FMPs belonging to the Welsh Affairs
OL,9,FSelect Committee along with the
OL,10,FPrisons Minister, Lord James Timpson.
OL,12,FThe Labour minister Lord Timpson was
OL,13,Fasked by the committee's chair, Ruth
OL,14,FJones, if he agreed with his
OL,15,FConservative predecessor who'd told
OL,16,FMPs that there were no plans to cancel
OL,17,FG4S' contract to run Parc.
